issue.body:
Scenario:
I want to build multiple versions of the same box, but different distros and different providers. For instance, I want to do a 3x3 matrix of boxen: {qemu, virtualbox, vmware} x fedora 3{2,1,0}.

The only values that will vary between the qemu boxen is iso_{checksum,url}. Meanwhile, it would be great to not have to repeat myself with the URLs, checksum, and boot commands, either, for each provider.

What I would like to do:

```
locals {
  qemu = { ... }
  virtualbox = { ... }
  fedora = { ... }
  fedora_32 = { ... }
  // etc
}

source "qemu" "fedora-32" merge(local.qemu, local.fedora, local.fedora_32)
source "vritualbox-iso" "fedora-32" merge(local.qemu, local.fedora, local.fedora_32)
// etc
```

Or something similar. It doesn't seem possible to do this. Doing this, or variations on it leads to:

```
Error: Invalid block definition

  on config/source_fedora.pkr.hcl line 8:
   8: source "qemu" "fedora-32" local.qemu_fedora_32

Either a quoted string block label or an opening brace ("{") is expected here.
```
